-- Confidence in Italy Returned in Financial Markets, Public Debt Chief Says
-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2012-02-18T17:14:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-18/confidence-in-italy-returned-in-financial-markets-public-debt-chief-says.html
Maria Cannata,  Italy ’s director of
public debt, said investors have regained confidence in Italy.  “The market has again confidence towards Italy, it
realized the country has taken its commitments very seriously,”
Cannata said at an event in Parma, Italy, today. She also said
that investors from  Europe , the U.S. and  Asia  are buying Italian
 government bonds .  To contact the reporter on this story:
